    "And there are some handy rules like, a sentence should always have a verb, and check subject-verb agreement-it can't be \"he walk\" in some dialects of English, though it can be in others.Nevertheless, there are subtleties that school grammars miss.",
    "These are three very different kinds of \"walk.\"",
    "Walking to work is goal and direction-oriented, from A to B.",
    "Walking the dog is from A and back to A.",
    "But when the dog is enthusiastically pulling at the leash, isn't the dog really walking its human carer?"
  ],
